<paragraph blockId="41.[151,1436,1506,1638]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[201,317,1543,1567]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" reason="1">Remarks.</emphasis>
Both sexes of this Central Asian species have the wings strongly shortened with reduced venation in their apical halves (S. Belokobylskij pers. obs.). The male has thickened veins and the pterostigma strongly enlarged.
